This Resource describes the attributes associated with a battery. The
Property "charge" is an integer showing the current battery charge
level as a percentage in the range 0 (fully discharged) to 100 (fully
charged). The Property "capacity" represents the total capacity of
battery in Amp Hours (Ah). The "charging" status and "discharging"
status are represented by boolean values set to "true" indicating
enabled and "false" indicating disabled. Low battery status is
represented by a boolean value set to "true" indicating low charge
level and "false" indicating otherwise, based upon the battery
